article.headline: Earley's double-double paces Commodores
article.story:
SAVANNAH, Ga. (AP) -- Ashley Earley had 17 points and 13 rebounds
for her second straight double-double, and led No. 14 Vanderbilt to
a 61-28 victory Monday night over mistake-plagued Savannah State.

The Commodores swarmed from the opening tip-off and smothered
the Tigers, creating turnover after turnover. Vanderbilt (2-0)
executed two successful traps, forced one over-and-back call, and
had multiple steals in the opening minutes of the game.

Dee Davis finished with five of the Commodores' 15 steals.

Midway through the first half, Vanderbilt led 19-2 and held a
35-13 lead into the break.

Abi Ramsey had three 3-pointers in the first half for Vanderbilt
and finished with 13 points. Carla Thomas added 11

Savannah State (1-1) was led by Kermetris Hill with nine points.
